From all the "canon" Peaty studies, my favorite is still the one where they inject eggs with extra glucose and the chicken comes out smarter with a bigger brain and grows more intelligent, because it's the one explicitly not about healing disease, but going further beyond nature.

All the wonderful ones about methylene blue and dementia are insanely useful to know, but this one is incredibly simple and still shows a state of health is not an objective set in stone thing and you can push organisms to higher stages outside of baseline limitations forever.

The endgoal of medicine as a science is not just "prevention of disease" perpetually maintained, but actually raising the standards to where current normal people would be seen as pathologically mentally disabled. "They that be whole need not a physician, but they that are sick."
